= The <span style="color: #c00000;">**PKI**</span> Central Comitee Plenum

Ever since the 1948 Madiun Uprising, which resulted in the death of its principal leaders, the <span style="color: #c00000;">**PKI**</span> has been in a position of semi-illegality, and labeled as a traitor to the Republic's unity during the struggle period. In addition, its member count has been diminished to a mere three thousand and has been pushed to insignificance.

But that may change. After the Madiun Affair, the surviving leaders of the early days of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**PKI**</span>, men like Tan Ling Djie and Alimin, were being sidelined by a group of younger leaders, self-styled as the "Leninist Wing". The faction is led by D.N. Aidit, backed by other prominent figures such as Njoto, M.H. Lukman, and Sadisman. Since August 1950, the group published articles in the party's theoretical journal, <span class="tooltip-text" title="The Red Star">*Bintang Merah*</span>, critizing the party's strategies and called greater attention to party theory. Its circulation dramatically increased, so as <span style="color: #c00000;">**PKI**</span> membership.

- @aidit: Aidit steps on the podium..

@aidit
on-arrival: pki_leader = "D.N. Aidit"; workers_pki += 10
face-image: img/aidit-raised.jpg

In a recent plenum, the central comittee has elected a politbureau consisting of five members including D.N. Aidit as First Secretary with Tan Ling Djie and Alimin relegated to minor positions within the party. It is clear that this is the result of months of work by Aidit's faction influencing the party behind the scenes.

Now with Aidit at the helm, the <span style="color: #c00000;">**PKI**</span> begins its "rejuvenation". As soon as the Aidit leadership had established firm control over the lower organizations of the Party, it moved to expel and purge members deemed as 'trotskyist and adventurist' and cleanse the organs of the party of any remaining opposition.

- @root: Worrying..